<div id="review_2822941767" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2822941767" />
    <a title="Anthony Peter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25481916-anthony-peter"><img alt="Anthony Peter" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2822941767?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anthony Peter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anthony Peter" href="/user/show/25481916-anthony-peter">Anthony Peter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780436140907" href="/book/show/984062.Reflections_on_The_Name_of_the_Rose">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2822941767" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14971284723792770287">I found this was enormously helpful in explaining the rationale behind many of the things that I found difficult about &apos;The Name of the Rose&apos; and that it offered insights into the art of fiction as well.<br/><br/>I was muddled by Eco&apos;s reflections on post-modernism. I&apos;m muddled by post-modernism anyway. In fact, I had wondered, when reading TNOTR, if Eco was taking a potshot at post-modernism and pedantry.<br/><br/>Be that as it may, this a book I&apos;ll re-read more often that TNOTR.</span>
  <span id="freeText14971284723792770287" style="display:none">I found this was enormously helpful in explaining the rationale behind many of the things that I found difficult about 'The Name of the Rose' and that it offered insights into the art of fiction as well.<br /><br />I was muddled by Eco's reflections on post-modernism. I'm muddled by post-modernism anyway. In fact, I had wondered, when reading TNOTR, if Eco was taking a potshot at post-modernism and pedantry.<br /><br />Be that as it may, this a book I'll re-read more often that TNOTR.</span>
