<span id="freeTextContainer2541882746533696804">Reading this short book I could apprecieted the author´s purpose to explain his personal writing procces that produced this complex novel. Certainly, he is a completed erudite on the subjet, and all the references given about de sources, styles, characters or some language expressions he used, are so useful to the writers`s world in order to created a new work in a seriously way.<br/>However, I got absolutely dissapointed, because my original purpose were looking for the kind of interpretation the au</span>
  <span id="freeText2541882746533696804" style="display:none">Reading this short book I could apprecieted the author´s purpose to explain his personal writing procces that produced this complex novel. Certainly, he is a completed erudite on the subjet, and all the references given about de sources, styles, characters or some language expressions he used, are so useful to the writers`s world in order to created a new work in a seriously way.<br />However, I got absolutely dissapointed, because my original purpose were looking for the kind of interpretation the author had in his mind, and discover the effects he tried to produce on the readers. According that he explained at the beginning of the text, must be every reader who has to elaborated his own interpretations, that can be so differents as various are the point of view people have.<br />Now I have understood that my vision, opinions and interpretation is my own work. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2541882746533696804" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
