              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14688803739105618038">This was actually a fantastic companion piece to Name of the Rose—Eco describes a ton of background for the book, including why he chose to set it in November 1327 and why the library was a labyrinth. My favorite bit was something along the lines of &quot;Not having an abbey burn down is like having a book set in WWII without any battles.&quot; Cracked me up.</span>
  <span id="freeText14688803739105618038" style="display:none">This was actually a fantastic companion piece to Name of the Rose—Eco describes a ton of background for the book, including why he chose to set it in November 1327 and why the library was a labyrinth. My favorite bit was something along the lines of "Not having an abbey burn down is like having a book set in WWII without any battles." Cracked me up.</span>
